\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b 8-11}). {\b V. daenzeri} group. Basal leaves 9-22 × 1·5-5 cm, oblong- to obovate-oblanceolate, lyrate to pinnatisect, with 4-10 pairs of coarsely and irregularly incise-dentate lobes. Inflorescence lax; pedicels 5-35 mm. Calyx 3-4 mm. Fertile stamens 4, with or without a staminode, the lower with shortly decurrent anthers; filament-hairs violet. Style 5-10 mm.
